Function Description

TX : Transmit

RX : Receive. Always use a level converter for incoming data. This device is not 5V tolerant.

CH_PD : Chip enable. Should be high for normal operation.
• 0 – Disabled
• 1 – Enabled

RST : External reset.
• 0 – Reset
• 1 – Normal

GPIO 0 : Should be high on boot, low for flash update.

GPIO 2 : Should be high on boot.

VCC : 3.3V

GND : Ground
